Our top story in eastern bosnia reports of panic as the besieged muslim enclave of srebrenica appears to be on the verge of falling to bosnian serb forces .
Ham radio reports from within the area say serbs are expected to capture srebrenica any time now .
The new york times reports that muslim defenders could surrender as early as noon on friday local time in exchange for the safe evacuation of the sixty thousand muslim civilians trapped in the enclave .
A u. n. aid convoy left srebrenica on thursday with only five elderly women aboard after local leaders blocked a mass evacuation of refugees .
Meanwhile nato planes enforcing a u. n. no fly zone over bosnia tracked two unidentified aircraft in the zone on thursday but could not intercept them .
The war in bosnia is taking a terrible toll on the country's children .
Some wounded children who were evacuated from srebrenica on tuesday are receiving medical care in the town of tuzla .
But as paul davies reports some of them are scarred for life .
